</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">Epimedium dolichostemon</taxonomicName>
Stearn, Kew Bull., 45(4): 685. 1990. Type: China. Chongqing: Shizhu, alt. 150 m, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ogisu s. n.</emphasis>
(holotype, K!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He, Probst &amp; W. F. Xu" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dewuense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewuense">Epimedium dewuense</taxonomicName>
S.Z. He, Probst &amp; W.F. Xu, Acta Bot. Yunnan. 25(3): 281. 2003. Syn. nov. Type: China. Guizhou: Dejiang, in thickets on slopes, alt. 1350 m, 19 Apr. 2002, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">S.Z. He</emphasis>
&amp; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">W.F. Xu 2419</emphasis>
(holotype, GZTM!; isotype, KUN!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Herbs 30-50 cm tall. Rhizome compact. Leaves basal or cauline, trifoliolate; leaflets narrowly ovate or lanceolate, 8-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4.5 cm, apex long acuminate, margin spinous-serrate with the spines 0.5-1.5 mm, base deeply cordate with lobes acute or rounded, those of lateral leaflets very oblique, leathery, adaxially glabrous or pubescent, abaxially glaucous, glabrous or pubescent. Flowering stem with 2 opposite or rarely alternate leaves. Inflorescence paniculate, 15-20 cm long, 35-70-flowered, glabrous or glandular pubescent; pedicels 1-3 cm. Flowers ca. 2 cm in diam. with spreading inner sepals. Outer sepals purplish with margin white, outer pair ovate-oblong, 3.5-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-2.5 mm, apex obtuse, inner pair ovate, 4-5.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.8-3.5 mm, apex obtuse. Inner sepals white, narrowly elliptic or lanceolate, 8-14 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-5.5 mm, apex acuminate. Petals reddish purple, cucullate, much shorter than inner sepals, 3-4 mm, with blunt incurved spur and slight lamina base. Stamens conspicuously prolonged, ca. 8 mm; anthers ca. 2.5 mm; filaments 4.5-5 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="distribution and habitat">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in Chongqing, northeastern Guizhou, and western Hubei, and usually occurs in forests, thickets, and weedy slopes, at elevations of 800 to 1400 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers from March to April, and fruits from April to May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="iucn red list category">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">IUCN Red List category.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be designated as nearly threatened (NT) according to IUCN Red List criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, U. K." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" refId="B3" refString="IUCN, 2013. The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2013.9. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, U.K., http://www.iucnredlist.org/ [accessed: 6 June 2014]" title="The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2013.9" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" year="2013">IUCN 2013</bibRefCitation>
), because of exploitation for medicinal use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<bibRefCitation author="He, SZ" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Yunnanica" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="281 - 282" refId="B2" refString="He, SZ, Xu, WF, 2003. A new species of Epimedium (Berberidaceae) from Guizhou, China. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 25: 281 - 282" title="A new species of Epimedium (Berberidaceae) from Guizhou, China." volume="25" year="2003">He and Xu (2003)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He, Probst &amp; W. F. Xu" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dewuense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<pageBreakToken pageId="8" pageNumber="9" start="start">Epimedium</pageBreakToken>
dewuense
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species based only on the comparison with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium sagittatum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium sagittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but not with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He, Probst &amp; W. F. Xu" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dewuense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dewuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two species can be distinguished by the shape and indumentum of leaflets: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears narrowly ovate leaves glabrous on both sides, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He, Probst &amp; W. F. Xu" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dewuense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dewuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has wider leaves pubescent on both sides (
<bibRefCitation author="Stearn, WT" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="682 - 692" publicationUrl="10.2307/4113877" refId="B6" refString="Stearn, WT, 1990. Epimedium dolichostemon (Berberidaceae) and other Chinese species of Epimedium. Kew Bulletin 45 (4): 682 - 692, DOI: 10.2307/4113877" title="Epimedium dolichostemon (Berberidaceae) and other Chinese species of Epimedium." url="10.2307/4113877" volume="45" year="1990">Stearn 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="He, SZ" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Yunnanica" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="281 - 282" refId="B2" refString="He, SZ, Xu, WF, 2003. A new species of Epimedium (Berberidaceae) from Guizhou, China. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 25: 281 - 282" title="A new species of Epimedium (Berberidaceae) from Guizhou, China." volume="25" year="2003">He and Xu 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Based on investigations in herbaria and the field, morphological variation of leaflets between the two species is continuous, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He, Probst &amp; W. F. Xu" authorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dewuense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dewuense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dewuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here treated as a new synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium dolichostemon" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichostemon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium dolichostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
